message.content:
Analysis of the Main Target Image
---------------------------------
• Overall there are two separate sub‐structures, one on the left and one on the right.  
• Left Sub‐Structure  
  – Total of 3 blocks in 2 layers.  
  – Bottom Layer: A single red arch block.  
  – Top Layer: Two cubes side‐by‐side on top of the arch; the left cube is blue, the right cube is yellow.  

• Right Sub‐Structure  
  – Total of 4 blocks in 3 layers.  
  – Bottom Layer: Two orange cylinders lying next to each other.  
  – Middle Layer: A green rectangular block laid across (bridging) the two cylinders.  
  – Top Layer: An orange wedge set on top of the green rectangle.  

Selecting Required Blocks from the Dictionary
--------------------------------------------
From the block‐dictionary image, the following indices match the shape/orientation exactly (no re‐orientation allowed):

• Left Sub‐Structure  
  1. Red arch block → Index 1  
  2. Blue cube → Index 4  
  3. Yellow cube → Index 7  

• Right Sub‐Structure  
  4. Orange cylinder (×2) → Index 11 used twice  
  5. Green rectangular block → Index 10  
  6. Orange wedge → Index 15  

Assembly Order
--------------
{  
  Step1: Move block with index 1,  
  Step2: Move block with index 4,  
  Step3: Move block with index 7,  
  Step4: Move block with index 11,  
  Step5: Move block with index 11,  
  Step6: Move block with index 10,  
  Step7: Move block with index 15  
}
